Title: Sommore -the Queen Stand Alone

reviewText: I was on Amazon looking for Katt Williams and Sommore popped up as something else to check out. I read the reviews and decided to pick it up. I was not sure what to expect but it was actually pretty funny. I would definitely recommend it for anyone who enjoys good standup comedy. Be warned, she curses and talks about the things that people go through in life from being a child through their adult hood. If you are looking at comedy videos trying to decide what you should get, I would suggest you pick up Sommore for a real good laugh. Set the mood....Tell the kids to go into the other room, pour you some Hennessy, burn you some incense and get ready to laugh! YMMV...NEOSOUL06.

Title: Sommore -the Queen Stand Alone

reviewText: I didn't have to preview the DVD because after all, it was Sommore, one of the original Queens of Comedy. I make it a point to check out her show whenever she comes to my area.  She's had funnier rooutines but this DVD has its moments.  The funniest bit is when she's talking about partying with her hood girls and the girls from the office.  That was hillarious.  I hope she puts out another one soon. All in all it's entertaining, IT'S SOMOORE!
Title: Sommore -the Queen Stand Alone
